\fs48 \cf7 \cb8 Question text\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf7 \cb8 Discuss in which situations you would use asymmetric key ciphers. As part of your answer explain how these are used to provide confidentiality, integrity and authentication.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 Asymmetric key ciphers such as RSA, are often used as encryption to securely establish keys for a symmetric cipher between two parties, which will be used to actually encrypt and transmit the data. This is owing to the long keys and complex mathematical functions used in asymmetric key ciphers as opposed to symmetric keys which typically have shorter keys and are relatively less taxing to compute.\cb1 \
\cb3 Asymmetric key ciphers can be used first and foremost to ensure Confidentiality; sender may encrypt information with the intended recipients public key, and only those in possession of the corresponding private key would be able to see the information.\cb1 \
\cb3 Integrity and Authentication are ensured by creating a hash of the message to be sent, which is then encrypted using the sender's private key and sent along with the message. The recipient decrypts the hash using the sender's public key, computes the hash of the received message and compares them. If they are the same the recipient knows that the message has not been tampered with and that it genuinely came from the sender.\'a0\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs48 \cf9 \cb10 Feedback\cb1 \
