\fs32 \cf7 \cb8 Discuss the key differences between an SSL portal VPN and an SSL tunnel VPN.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 An SSL portal VPN provides access to web-based service through an SSL connection between a server and a user's web browser. \'a0Tunnel vpn provides access also to non-web based services and requires the browser to support active content such as ActiveX and Javascript.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs48 \cf9 \cb10 Feedback\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\i\fs32 \cf9 \cb10 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
An SSL portal VPN allows a user to use a single standard SSL connection to a Web site to securely access multiple network services. The site accessed is typically called a portal because it has a single page that leads to many other resources. SSL portal VPNs work with essentially any modern Web browser.
\i0 \cb1 \
\ls3\ilvl0
\i \cb10 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
An SSL tunnel VPN allows a user to use a typical Web browser to securely access multiple network services through a tunnel that is running under SSL. SSL tunnel VPNs require that the Web browser be able to handle specific types of active content (e.g., Java, JavaScript, Flash, or ActiveX) and that the user be able to run them. The tunneling in an SSL tunnel VPN allows a wide variety of protocols and applications to be run through it. For example, essentially any protocol that runs over TCP or UDP can be tunneled through such a gateway, making the remote user\'92s experience of the protected network very similar to being directly on the network
\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

