\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf7 \cb8 Discuss\'a0strengths and weakness of IPSec VPN solution.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 IPsec provides a secure tunnel between networks or between a single host and a network, the secure tunnel ensures confidentiality of data end to end and anonymity of transmission as IP headers are encrypted along with the data. IPsec is a robust and versatile solution as It is not restricted to a single suite of protocols, and can be configured with different hashing and encryption protocols.\cb1 \
\cb3 A disadvantage is that it encrypting and decrypting all packets flowing across the connection is very processing power intensive and can cause security breaches of one network to spread to other networks connected by site-to-site VPN.\'a0\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs48 \cf9 \cb10 Feedback\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf9 \
\cb10 IPsec was originally designed to provide point-to-point, always-on connections between remote sites and the central office resource. The clients in this case could be branch offices or vendors. The protocol is designed to work further down the network stack (layer 3) and can be used to transmit any IP-based protocol, irrespective of the application generating the traffic.\cb1 \
\cb10 IPsec\'91s key strength lies in its ability to provide a permanent connection between locations. Any IP-based protocol could be tunneled through it. This makes IPsec an attractive alternative to an expensive leased line or a dedicated circuit. IPsec's application-agnostic design is also its weakness, however though it provides authentication, authorization and encryption, while basically extending the corporate network to any remote user, it does not have the ability to restrict access to resources at a granular level.\'a0\cb1 \
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

